com.solvvy.cluster

Class MahoutClusterer<T extends Scoreable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.solvvy.cluster.MahoutClusterer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements to be clustered by this.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clusterer<T>

    public class MahoutClusterer<T extends Scoreable<T>>
extends Object
implements Clusterer<T>
    An implementation of the Clusterer interface using Mahout's cluster data structures and canopying and k-means algorithms.

    This class is not thread-safe; only one set of elements should be clustered at a time with it.

        public MahoutClusterer(Featurizer<T> featuresForClustering,
                       Vectorizer vectorizer,
                       FeatureSetClassifier<?> stage2Classifier,
                       ClusterFeaturizerFunction<T> featuresOfCluster)
        Construct a new MahoutClusterer.
        Parameters:
        featuresForClustering - a Featurizer that generates each element's features used to cluster them.
        vectorizer - a Vectorizer that generates each element's feature vector from its cluster-feature-set.
        stage2Classifier - a classifier used to generate element scores from the union set of each element's features and the features of the cluster they are contained in.
        featuresOfCluster - a function used after clustering that produces a stage2 featurizer for elements of a cluster.
